The paper proposes a novel method for learning better latent representations using neural networks. This falls under the category of machine learning, specifically deep learning, which is covered by cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also mentions the use of semantic perturbation to enhance the representational power of the learned latent features, which is related to natural language processing and computer vision, covered by cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Finally, the paper discusses the experimental results and provides t-SNE visualization, which is related to artificial intelligence and data visualization, covered by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
